The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

                                        Archives
                                                                                                                                    Five killed in mishaps

   A STAFF REPORTER
        
	The last day of 2007 claimed five lives on the streets across the city. Among the victims was an infant.
 
	A speeding private bus on route 3C/1 ran over two pavement-dwellers mdash; Durga Bhattacharjee, 55, and grand-daughter Puja, 4 mdash; on Vivekanada Road around 11.40am on Monday.
 
	The two were taken to NRS Medical College and Hospital, where Puja was declared dead. Durga died a few hours later. Police said the driver and the conductors fled.
 
	 ldquo;The driver lost control after taking a sharp turn and ran over the duo, rdquo; said an officer of Amherst Street police station.
 
	Jatai Mondal, 35, died after being knocked down by a Maruti van near Chingrihata in the morning. Police said Mondal was crossing the road. He was taken to a hospital where he was declared dead. The driver fled with his vehicle.
 
	An unidentified man was injured in the head and chest after being hit by a vehicle near Kidderpore bridge around 11am. A police patrol team took him to SSKM Hospital, where he was pronounced dead.
 
	Four pedestrians were injured after being knocked down by a speeding private bus on route 72 at the crossing of CR Avenue and Mahatma Gandhi Road around 7.30am. The four were taken to Medical College and Hospital, where Satyajit Pyne, 55, was declared dead. He was a resident of Beniapukur.
 
	 ldquo;It was a case of rash driving. The driver did not slam the brakes, rdquo; said an officer of Jorasanko police station.
 
	Netaji Pathak, 50, was critically injured after being hit by an unidentified vehicle on the eastern slope of Howrah bridge around 8.15am. Pathak, an Amta resident, has been admitted to Medical College and Hospital.
                                                                           
